Memo: Received on: 2024-10-10<p/> Description: Tortie Spayed Female Domestic Shorthair Cat<p/> Age: 1 YEAR 1 MONTH<p/> Adoption Fee: $30<p/> Current Location: In RASKC Foster Home <p/>Hello there, My name is Torta.<p/><p/>I'm currently in a foster home. This is what my current foster parents have to say about me:<p/><p/>Hi, my name is Torta!<p/>I was living at a foster home with my brother Spatlo since we were both scared of humans, but we eventually learned how nice humans can be! <p/>Both me and my sibling are high energy kitties who love chasing each other and playing with toys (especially wands!). We are also highly food motivated and have been caught multiple times biting through food bags! At our foster home we did a good job of coexisting with the senior cats, outside of stealing their food at times!<p/><p/>Of the two of us, I`m the more courageous and cleverer kitty,I`m easy to handle and pick up! When I first met the older cats, my foster dad would often have to hold me back to ensure I didn`t scare them. I also have a reputation as a troublemaker as I`m the one who finds food bags and starts breaking into them! But I`m also a purry kitty who loves head scritches and lying on a warm lap! When our foster dad was using his standing desk, we would often grab onto his leg as we wanted him to sit down with us!<p/><p/>We would probably like a quieter home as we still are shy around most people and new situations. I would like to be adopted with my brother Spatlo so we can continue to play and snuggle together!<p/>

Cheddar enjoys pets and belly rubs but is still hesitant about kisses and being picked up.<p/>Cheddar has a fondness for toys with fake fur and he is OBSESSED with the cat toy called Da Bird , a feather wand toy.  This toy has helped him become comfortable with humans.  He enthusiastically uses scratching posts and cat trees. Cheddar has been fostered with a kitten, Brie, (A717541) who is younger than him and they have somewhat bonded because of their playful nature in a foster home with older cats.   Because of his playful nature he will do best in a home with another cat of the same age or younger.<p/>Being fostered in a home with older cats Cheddar has learned when it is okay to approach them and when he needs to back off.  Cheddar has also been fostered in a home with an 80 lbs. cat friendly dog.  He is used to and okay with having his butt sniffed and comfortable being around the dog but no real interaction between them.  Cheddar has a cute trill sound when he is playing or investigating.  The only time Ive heard him cry is when I am getting his meals ready.  Obviously encouraging me to work faster.<p/>Cheddar will need a patient, understanding family willing to give him time to bond. The reward will be sharing life with an adorable, fun-loving cat who has already shown tremendous growth in his ability to trust and connect.<p/><p/>Please check Finding4everhomes on Instagram for more photos and videos of Cheddar.<p/>https://gcc02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FDGSShttRRoO%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_web_copy_link&data=05%7C02%7Cchameleonsvc%40kingcounty.gov%7C6ea16b2437fd4df5262408dd51816875%7Cbae5059a76f049d7999672dfe95d69c7%7C0%7C0%7C638756338430899346%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=g0askBi47XnkYc17ZiezNucNEuj2TOyw2qjB%2FAHuGDM%3D&reserved=0<p/>
